  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PRCS Total Communication School</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Palestinian Red Crescent Society and Netherlands Red Cross Society</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The current space is not enough to provide all facilities for the implementation of different activities. Therefore PRCS has been constructing a new four floor building for the school to provide enough and secure space for
the deaf students and to establish an inclusive kindergarten for the deaf, hard of hearing and post cochlear implant children.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will provide the necessary funding for the 2nd phase of the construction: Developing sections in the school</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Total communication school, is one of the four PRCS schools for deaf children and adolescents in Palestine. The school implements the national curriculum assigned by the Ministry of Education while adapting the total communication Project in teaching the deaf. When started in 1993, it was the only school that implemented this inclusive program combining all means of communication with the deaf (sign language, lip reading, auditory training, speech training, reading and writing) in addition to facial expressions and body language. The current place of the school is located in the 4th floor of PRCS headquarters in  Al-Bireh City with a space of about 1100 square meters.</narrative>
  </description>
